{
  "texts": [
    "However, if the market moves towards individualised risk assessments, it may necessitate widespread adoption of this practice to avoid retaining expensive risks at too low a price point.",
    "If this is the case, further regulation may be required to manage this practice within the context of consumer protection.",
    "However, risk mitigation techniques can be applied, such as offering specific types of insurance to high-risk individuals.",
    "This notion could be applied to providing specialised cover to those identified as very high risk when conducting an individual risk assessment.",
    "An example of targeted insurance is diabetes insurance where premium rates are revised annually based on average blood sugar levels over the past 3 months and cannot increase past the premium rate at inception (see, e.g."
  ]
}